Sentence: Kim Go-eun (Korean: 김고은; born October 22, 1983), better known by the stage name Byul (Korean: 별; lit.
star), is a South Korean singer.
She debuted in 2002 with the album December 32.
Her debut album was released on October 10, 2002.
It was announced at the end of January 2009 that Primary, her fifth album, would be released the following month.
Teaser posters were distributed in 7-11 stores.
On August 15, 2012, it was announced that Byul was to marry Haha, South Korean singer, actor and cast member of the variety show Running Man, on November 30, 2012.
The couple welcomed their first child, a son named Dream, on July 9, 2013.
Their second son, Soul, was born on March 22, 2017.
Their third child, a daughter, named Song, was born on July 15, 2019.
